Key Investment Highlights

This property fund enables wholesale and pre-approved investors to have a 30% profit share exposure in an architecturally designed project in Carrara, QLD.

The Offer

  • 30% profit share exposure with no cap. The return on investment is forecasted at $3,059,886, indicating a projected IRR of 25.5%*.
  • Rare, elevated site with 360˚ views in Carrara, one of Australia’s highest-growth suburbs, with 37.4% capital growth.**
  • Strong rental yield at 5.4% p.a.**, higher than Sydney, Melbourne & Brisbane.
  • A commitment to ecological restoration with 80% of the land to be rehabilitated as a public conservation space.
  • A staged low-rise development over a 24-month term mitigates investment risks.

*All financial figures and timeframes are forecasts based on the latest available data and can vary.
**Australian Bureau of Statistics & Broad Property Research and Advisory

The Development

This elevated site with views towards Broadbeach and the Gold Coast hinterland will be developed into 59 high-end, architecturally designed townhomes inside a private, exclusive gated community.

Creating a sense of place, these luxury homes will be complemented by communal recreation facilities, including a resort-style pool and outdoor kitchen as well as an expansive private conservation area and walking tracks.

A significant portion of the property (~23.88ha) will be rehabilitated by planting ~50,000 native trees and plants, eradicating the area of invasive weeds and installing nesting boxes for native birds, before being transferred to council as public conservation space.

Another 7,993m² will be retained by the development as an environmental covenant area, protecting the existing vegetation for the residents’ use and benefit. We envision incorporating walking trails and quiet spots for relaxing amongst the trees into this area, promoting it as a fauna habitat.

Luxury Dwellings

Positioned at the end of the cul-de-sac at Baltimore Court in Carrara, our upcoming development includes a total of 59 modern luxury homes, 53 of which are premium 4-bedroom layouts and 6 with 3 bedrooms. Each architect-designed home will boast a double garage and 2.5 bathrooms, along with a multi-purpose room in the 4-bedroom homes. These have been meticulously designed to suit different needs. The majority of these homes will be in duplex formation, sprinkled with a handful of fourplexes.

The Location

The location's charm lies in its 360-degree views towards Broadbeach and the Gold Coast Hinterland, as well as its leafy pockets of protected native vegetation. It has easy access to the M1 motorway and Nielsen’s Road, as well as nearby amenities, all of which contribute to the site’s suitability for a residential community of this scale.

We've taken care to blend architectural aesthetics, landscaping, and street network design within the site boundaries, ensuring minimal impact on the natural surroundings and the neighbouring residences. The design guarantees a visually pleasing modern appeal, with premium architectural elements adding character to the buildings.

This luxury residential community will organically follow the site's natural contours and the internal street curve, providing residents with incredible views. The homes, nestled within the existing landscape, will form a unique enclave that gracefully opens up to the natural surroundings. The thoughtful layout optimises ventilation and reduces the bulk of the buildings while respecting the site's natural environment. This project promises not only a stylish living space but a harmonious existence with nature.

componentInstanceProperties.value: Leading this Development

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value: Brad Beh is VentureCrowd’s Senior Development Manager. With over 29 years of experience in property development, he has specialised in infill land subdivisions, townhouse and apartment projects across SEQ over the past 20+ years. His tenure as Partner/General Manager at EkkoPoint Properties saw him supervise the delivery, sale and settlement of property ventures totalling over $260M. His track record includes successful consultancy roles for Gallery Group and the establishment of his own development firm, Bramick. Currently, Bramick is engaged in highly technical projects, including the development of 20 luxury townhouses in Albany Creek and a DA-approved 9-lot subdivision in Carseldine, underscoring Brad's commitment to innovative property solutions.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value: David leads VentureCrowd's Property Team. David is a former lawyer and a senior property development executive with over 25 years of experience with some of Australia’s leading property organisations. David was previously the Queensland General Manager for Grocon, State Director for Multiplex Developments and Project Director for Laing O’Rourke. David specialises in strategy, acquisitions, disposals, structuring, project initiation and approvals of institutional-grade real estate assets across the commercial, residential, retail and hospitality categories.

Green Futures Initiative

VentureCrowd believes that property development projects should be profitable while also creating dynamic residential communities that simultaneously enhance residents’ health and well-being and reduce harmful impacts on the environment.

This project is perfectly aligned with our environmental ethos. The sustainably designed master plan of this residential community considers the environmental, social and economic impacts of the project and the individual dwellings.

Sustainable design principles include the ability to:

  • Optimise site potential
  • Minimise non-renewable energy consumption
  • Use of environmentally preferable products
  • protect and conserve water
  • Enhance indoor environmental quality and liveability
  • Optimise operational and maintenance practices

Carrara is part of our Green Futures Initiatives, with 80% of the land forcast to be rehabilitated as a public conservation space. As part of that, we aim to plant an estimated 50,000 native trees and plants and install nesting boxes for native birds.

Market Drivers

Carrara is well located in the Northern Growth Corridor approximately 8 minutes from the beaches of Broadbeach and 55 minutes from the Brisbane CBD.

It has the largest market in SEQ with over 500 stalls and is the home of the Carrara stadium which hosted the Gold Coast Commonwealth Games in 2018, and now as the Metricon Stadium, it is currently the home of the Gold Coast Suns AFL and AFLW teams, and hosts cricket, rugby and other sports as well as large expos and concerts.

Carrara boasts excellent public and private schools, plentiful retail facilities as well as the famous Palm Meadows Golf Course.

Financial Forecast

The project is forecasting total development costs of $71,503,336 and conservatively forecasting net sale proceeds of $81,702,955, resulting in an expected development profit of $10,199,619. Profit is not capped, so if the sale prices are higher, returns will be higher also.

The Fund

VentureCrowd Trust No. 0650 (Carrara Qld Development Pty Ltd) (Fund) is structured as an unregistered wholesale unit trust, the trustee of which is VentureCrowd Nominees Pty Ltd (ACN 166 599 140).

Investors will acquire D Class Units in the Fund at an issue price of $1.00 per Unit. The Fund will acquire ordinary shares issued by Carrara Qld Development Pty Ltd (ACN 657 149 776) (SPV).

The Trustee will issue Units to investors in its capacity as an authorised representative of VentureCrowd Pty Ltd (ACN 166 598 849) under its Australian Financial Services License No.503381.

The Offer

VentureCrowd is raising up to $6,000,000 through the offer of D Class Units (at an issue price of $1.00 per Unit) in the VentureCrowd Trust No. 650 (Carrara Qld Development Pty Ltd) (Fund), an unregistered wholesale unit trust.

For VentureCrowd investors, this investment targets an Internal Rate of Return (IRR) of 25.5%*, based on 30% of the development profit (with a return on investment currently forecast to be $3,059,886). If less than $6,000,000 is raised through this class of units, the profit entitlement will be distributed pro rata.

Who Can Invest?
This offer is open to wholesale and pre-approved investors. If you have a wholesale investor certification, have assets of AUD $2.5 million or have a gross income of the last 2 financial years of at least AUD $250,000 per annum, this is probably applicable to you.

Additionally, if you are an experienced investor with multiple investments in venture capital or property, you may be qualified by our team as a wholesale investor after reviewing your documentation.

Fees and Expenses

The fees and expenses payable in connection with the management of the Fund are as follows:

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
The fees and expenses payable in connection with the management of the Fund are as follows:

  • Contribution Fee: 1.1% of your investment amount in the Fund, payable upon acceptance of your investment by the Trustee.
  • Management Fee: 1.65% p.a. of the Gross Asset Value of the Fund, payable by the Fund’s assets.
  • Expenses: estimated at 0.5% p.a. of the Gross Asset Value of the Fund, payable by the Fund’s assets.
  • Off-market Transfer Fee (if you wish to transfer your holding to someone else): $500 + 2% of the total amount transferred, unless the buyer is identified by you in advance.*

*If the buyer is identified by you in advance, the 2% fee does not apply. VentureCrowd cannot guarantee a purchaser for your holding

Why Invest Through VentureCrowd?

VentureCrowd is the leading digital investment platform for alternative assets. We find and fund the brightest and most innovative startups.

Our curation and due diligence is rigorous and our track record of success speaks for itself:

  • $20M+ total distributed to investors.

  • 73K+ members and counting.

  • Over $300,000,000 in capital raised since inception.

VentureCrowd is investor-led, which means we only list deals with secured professional external lead investors. Our investors then invest on the same economic terms as professional investors. If you invest in one of our deals you will receive equity or ownership in the company that is raising the capital. Not only will your investment come with lower fees and capital commitments, but it will also come with reduced deal complexity, and you’ll have access to alternative equity, property and credit opportunities on the same terms as professional lead investors.

  • Don't miss out, this investment opportunity could close fast! Invest now

Please note, the Fund Manager reserves the right to vary or cancel the Offer at any time, vary the amount raised under the Offer, vary or waive the Minimum Investment and close the Offer, without notice and without giving reasons.

Risks

Whilst the directors of the Fund Manager are experienced investment managers and the senior executives of the Development Manager have substantial experience in managing property development projects, there are always risks associated with development and construction which may, either directly or indirectly, result in reduced distributions and/or a loss of some of the capital value of an investment in the Fund.

Before deciding whether to subscribe for Units, you should consider whether an investment in this Fund, the underlying asset of which will be the Property, is suitable for you. If you are in doubt as to whether you should invest, please consult a suitably qualified professional advisor.

The key risks associated with investing in the Fund are set out in the Information Memorandum attached below and include the following:

  • a downturn in the general economic and market conditions in South-East Queensland;
  • unfavourable movements in interest rates, inflation or the unemployment rate;
  • changes to the law (including tax laws) and accounting rules;
  • industrial relations disputes and strikes;
  • natural disasters, including earthquakes, fire and storm;
  • social unrest, terrorist attack or war in Australia or overseas;
  • no guarantee of performance or return;
  • development costs and project expenditure being lower than forecast;
  • issues and delays with council;
  • related parties not performing; and
  • availability of construction funding.

Investors should read those documents before making a decision to invest and, if required, seek financial advice.
